03/03/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Prosecutors with the Special War Crimes Unit announced on Sunday (March 2nd) that they have indicted two Bosnian Serbs for war crimes committed years ago in the Nevesinje, Kalinovik, Gacko and Bileca municipalities. Krsto Savic Kico, 49, and Milko Mucibabic Mile, 57, were charged with crimes against humanity, including murder, systematic torture and forceful displacement of residents of those four municipalities from June 1992 to January 1993.
In other news, the BiH High Judicial and Prosecution Council appointed Milorad Barasin as interim chief prosecutor Monday. Barasin replaces Marinko Jurcevic, who has gone on indefinite sick leave. (Dnevni Avaz - 01/03/08; Fena, RTRS - 29/02/08)
